cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with tracking and semantic segmentation in real-world robotics applications using recurrent neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves robotics and machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of neural networks for tracking and classification makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves unsupervised learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of recurrent neural networks suggests that the paper could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
